urlencode deep "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
==============================================================

NAME
----

urlencode deep - Navigates through an array and encodes the values to be used in a URL.

SYNOPSIS
--------

Navigates through an array and encodes the values to be used in a URL.

Uses a callback to pass the value of the array back to the function as a
string.

USAGE
-----

` <?php urlencode_deep( $value ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$value` 
:   ([*array|string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Array.7Cstring "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) The array or string to be encoded.
    Default: *None*

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(array|string)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   \$value The encoded array (or string from the callback).

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [2.2](/Version_2.2 "Version 2.2")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`urlencode_deep()` is located in `wp-includes/formatting.php`

